<br>
A wizard is an offensive spellcaster, and I think it would be very cool if we could summon forth all of our magical energies in one massive strike on a mob.  A deadly maelstrom of offensive forces brought to bear upon a single point in a kamikaze style attack.<br>
<br>
The Rending Of The Cosmos<br>
Level 60<br>
Evocation<br>
Lure Based Single Target Direct Damage<br>
10 minute recast delay<br>
Costs 3000 mana.<br>
Causes a percentage of mob's hp's to be destroyed.<br>
Causes death of the wizard, exp permanently lost.<br>
<br>
The delay will prevent bind-rush abuse.<br>
<br>
We do 20k or so with bane on a single mob with over 100k hp's (roughly a max of 20% of its life), so perhaps a percentage for this spell should be in the 20-25% range.<br>
<br>
The loss of exp (a la necro Sacrifice) is the price for foolishly wielding such unrestrained power. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=deneteth>Deneteth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/20/01 2:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> I always thought it would be interesting to have a spell like that... a  &quot;heroic blow&quot; spell.<br>
<br>
Wouldn't it be great to stand alone in front of an ubermob while the rest of the group runs for its life and saving them by sacrificing oneself in one big DD? A bit like Gandalf did in the Moria.<br>
<br>
I'd prefer losing exp and saving ppl instead of losing exp running like a chicken...<br>
<br>
Of course one could argue that we have the evac line of spells to take care of desperate situations but that's far less fun :-)<br>
<br>
Deneteth<br>
33 wizard<br>
Morell Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaylorcoronis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maylor Coronis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/20/01 6:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> that does sound pretty sweet.  i always thought it would be cool if wizzies got like a HT or LoH.  More like the HT.  Once a day super damage for half the mana bar.<br>
<br>
The only thing about your spell that I see problems.  20% damage, as much as that might be, if things are going badly that you need to leave then i am not sure if 20% is going to be enough to make the shot.  Also, with a 10 min delay on that....the spell kills you, the delay would be kind of moot.  Yes it would prevent you form meming it real fast then casting it, but I think at the cost of your life it should be one of those no delay, no cast time...just like up the hands and watch the shit it the fan....although you really couldn't see how bad ass it is if you are dead.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><font color=#3399FF>Maylor Conornis<br/>
30th High Elven Wizard
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/21/01 2:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Change on a theme...</span><hr size=1> if it's a spell that's going to kill the caster, I'd think it should cost something like:<br>
3 or 4 dmg / mana point<br>
2 or 3 dmg / HP (since you ARE putting your lifeforce into this shot, you should get points for how healthy you are)<br>
and cost 2x or 3x of the XP of a normal death AND have the recast delay.<br>
<br>
So if you've got 3000 mana and 800 Hps, you'd do between 10600 and 14400 damage in a single cast, but it would seriously screw up your XP.  maybe the cost would even include sending you back to your starting point (not bind point).<br>
<br>
Of course, I've never seen the endgame, so I am just throwing out numbers. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 29th Season
<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath
<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sdogg>Sdogg</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/22/01 2:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> Also wouldn't mind seeing a spell that might be considered to function similarly to Evacuate.  Wizards are named Channelers for part of our career, and if we can drain group mana via Evacuate then why can't we channel group mana into an offensive blast?<br>
<br>
Damage would be a multiple based on the number of group members with sufficient mana.  For example, if the spell costs 300 mana and does 750dd and 3 members have 300 mana and the other 3 are either manaless tanks or have less than 300 mana left, then the standard damage for a cast would be 750x3=2250dd.<br>
<br>
The advantage in this is our ability to cast fire/ice/magic as appropriate against a resistant mob...so other group members who may not have the ability to damage a mob (mob resists fire, mage/ench in group have no ice-based spells) can be collectively represented by the wizard's superior channeling skills. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 185<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/22/01 2:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> Seems more like an ablility, and why does everyone keep saving these things for level 60? <p>
-I began my journey with the intent to save the world. I ended it, realizing the world did not wish to be saved.


Wizard of the 36th Reckoning</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 490<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/22/01 9:05 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Wizards are named Channelers for part of our career, and if we can drain group mana via Evacuate then why can't we channel group mana into an offensive blast?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I've always wondered why the characters are basically doing everything together by themselves in this game. I mean, sure, you buff or heal another player, but you don't do anything else.<br>
<br>
I think it'd be cool to be able to link minds, so all players in a group would use the same giant group mana pool. Or they'd all use the same HP pool. That would be cool. <br>
It'd be like those green construction transformers that each turned into a robot, and then they all combined into a bigger robot. That was cool... <p><center><IMG SRC=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/jarnin3dsig.jpg><br><center><Br><Br>Grand Master Fisherman<Br>Master Brewer<Br>Master Chef<Br>Master of Begging<Br><Br><b>DEATH TO AL`KABOR!</b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/24/01 11:08 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> I'd prefer this be an AoE thing replacing the current Al'Kabor series...<br>
<br>
1 group member does 1/2 current damage<br>
2 group members does normal current damage<br>
3 group members does 1.5x current damage<br>
4 group members does 2x current damage<br>
5 group members does 2.5x current damage<br>
full group = 3x current damage for all 5 MOBs under the spiral of al'kabor. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 29th Season
<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath
<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umaylorcoronis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maylor Coronis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/24/01 9:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> Now there is an idea.  Spells based on number of people in a group would make us worthy.  Hell if i knew there is a person out there who, in a group, could do an awesome amount of damage like that based on the number of people, i'd get him in right away.<br>
<br>
enchanter_01 says: &quot;mezzing a_mob&quot;<br>
meatshield_01 says: &quot;don't bother, let the wizzies take care of them in a few casts&quot;<br>
<br>
notice wizzies??  Funny how people don't have a problem with adding 2+ melees to a group.  Hell, I've been in groups where we had 3 wizzies and stuff dropped so fast with such little effort/mana it was incredible.  people just don't realized that a wizzy on his own isn't very efficient, but even with just 2 the wizzies together well make up for any single defficiency. <p><font color=#3399FF>Maylor Conornis<br/>
30th High Elven Wizard
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umerco81.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merco81</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/29/01 7:37 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> slight problem...</span><hr size=1> Don't get me wrong, I really like the idea of having the wizard's damage increased by the amount of people in a grp... but imagine a full grp of wizzies casting that exact same spell. The only way I can see this not being too overpowering is if the wizzie gets an aftereffect of being stunned or something like that for about 10 seconds or so. If they put a spell like that for wizzies, more then likely that will be the case. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/1/01 9:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: slight problem...</span><hr size=1> Then count it as &quot;other players who aren't wizards&quot; because wizards are good channelers, we can PREVENT others from using us in that way.  Problem solved, and no stun effect. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 29th Season
<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath
<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uhexored.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hexored</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 16<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/1/01 12:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> I see it:<br>
Warrior: Ok wizzy nuke this dragon<br>
Loading please wait ....<br>
<br>
Warrior: All warriors roll for armor. Clerics don't rezz wizzy he can gate here!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/1/01 1:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> Ahh, but if they don't protect us, we don't cast it.  It balances itself. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
<br>Wizard of the 29th Season
<br>High Councilman of the Nightwatch of Norrath
<br>"You look up overkill in the dictionary and there's a picture of Aniar lol" Lotta on Saryrn</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=holmiumelblastee>Holmium Elblastee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/2/01 4:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> The idea of not being able to get back exp sucks. Frankly, I don't want to go about willy nilly, sacrificing my hard earned exp. I wouldn't even get the spell.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#ffffff>(10/4/01 9:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just rambling...</span><hr size=1> You use it as a way of saving a group of friends in a dangerous situation, or in raid situations where XP isn't (supposedly) as sought after.  The &quot;can't get back XP thru a rez&quot; keeps us from using it all the time. <p><br>Aniar Orrenson
